3 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Firefighting training facility infrastructure grants authorization. (1)
4 The department is authorized to make up to $5 million in grants to local government firefighting authorities for
5 property acquisition, construction, space acquisition, remodeling, repairs, and the purchase of appliances and
6 equipment. The grants authorized in this section are subject to the conditions set forth in [section 5].
7 (2) The department shall receive proposals from local government firefighting authorities for
8 firefighting training facility infrastructure projects.
9 (3) Funding for projects may be provided only as long as there are sufficient funds available from
10 the amount that was deposited or transferred in the firefighting training facility infrastructure account for grants
11 established in [section 2]. Funding for these projects must be made available in the order that the grant
12 recipients satisfy the conditions described in [section 5].
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Eligibility -- submission deadline -- priority -- guidelines. (1) A local
15 government firefighting authority may apply to the department for firefighting training facility infrastructure grants
16 under [section 3].
17 (2) Local government firefighting authorities shall submit grant applications to the department in
18 order to be eligible for funding under [section 3].
19 (3) The department is authorized to adopt guidelines necessary to implement [sections 3 through
20 5].
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Condition of grants -- disbursement of funds. (1) The disbursement of
23 grant funds for the projects chosen by the department pursuant to [section 3] is subject to the following
24 conditions:
25 (a) for grants in an amount of $25,000 or more, the department may require a grant recipient to
26 provide a 1% match in cash or donated services to be eligible to receive a grant the grant recipient shall
27 document the availability of matching funds at least $1 in value for each $1 of the grant;
